body:
Only for certain values, I'm getting the following warning unexpectedly:
``Warning-REALCVT: Implicit conversion of real to integer``

I'm using the following version (on MacBook Air, which I installed via brew):
``Verilator 4.222 2022-05-02 rev UNKNOWN.REV``

Example code (this code is adopted from [here](https://www.chipverify.com/systemverilog/systemverilog-datatypes)):
```verilog
struct packed {
   int	coins;
   real	dollars;
} wallet;

initial begin
  wallet = '{5, 0.0};
  wallet = '{5, 2.0};
  wallet = '{5, -2.0};
  wallet = '{5, 2.5};
end
```

Verilator is ok with ``0.0`` and ``2.0``, but not with ``-2.0`` and ``2.5``, see below two warnings:
```
%Warning-REALCVT: bla.sv:22:17: Implicit conversion of real to integer
   22 |   wallet = '{5, -2.0};
      |                 ^
%Warning-REALCVT: bla.sv:23:17: Implicit conversion of real to integer
   23 |   wallet = '{5, 2.5};
      |                 ^~~
```

Any ideas?  Thank you!
